Last December I had gone to India (Mumbai) for about two weeks visit. (Thanks @pranphy) From the first day to the last day, this was the ONLY I song I listened with my earphones on. Travelling all those hours and days on the train, the local bus, the auto ride, the late night around Pawai, and the best moment when I reached the Zuhu Beach and finally that ocean... which connected myself with the earth, the rise and falls of life as the waves in the ocean, and this song.... Tu Chale, Sanga Chale Sabhi Gul..... I faced the ocean and turned to the far reaching horizon... which beyond thousands of miles connected to another part of the world where she was... And I missed her so badly.... The ocean was our separation.... but it was the ocean that connected... and the ocean was full of huge and small tides, ups and downs..... but whatever it was, was beautiful, rich and like ... enlightening.
